abstract: They had come from faraway states for country music. They were police officers, teachers, secretaries. Here are the stories of the 58 people who died.
snippet: They had come from faraway states for country music. They were police officers, teachers, secretaries. Here are the stories of the 58 people who died.
lead_paragraph: The night began as a celebration. Thousands gathered in Las Vegas for one last night of song at a long-awaited country music festival. They had driven in from towns all over California. They had flown in from Alaska, Tennessee, West Virginia. They were teachers, police officers, secretaries, retirees.

abstract: The league is trying to balance its players’ desire to raise awareness of social issues while accommodating fans who would prefer football to be just about football.
snippet: The league is trying to balance its players’ desire to raise awareness of social issues while accommodating fans who would prefer football to be just about football.
lead_paragraph: Faced with the prospect of another wave of sideline demonstrations at N.F.L. games this weekend, the league’s owners and players are wrestling with how to plot a path forward from one of the most divisive weekends it has seen.

abstract: The sport was not incidental to the doctrine of segregation. It was one of the pillars on which it rested.
snippet: The sport was not incidental to the doctrine of segregation. It was one of the pillars on which it rested.
lead_paragraph: “Wouldn’t you love to see one of these N.F.L. owners, when somebody disrespects our flag, to say, ‘Get that son of a bitch off the field right now, out, he’s fired.’” With those disparaging words, spoken Friday night at a campaign speech for a Senate candidate in Alabama, the president of the United States ignited a firestorm, which he continued to stoke on Twitter over the weekend.

headline_main: Politics Has Always Had a Place in Football

abstract: After the president took aim at N.F.L. players and the N.B.A. star Stephen Curry, athletes and celebrities reacted on Twitter with strong words.
snippet: After the president took aim at N.F.L. players and the N.B.A. star Stephen Curry, athletes and celebrities reacted on Twitter with strong words.
lead_paragraph: The days of superstar athletes being unwilling to speak their minds for fear of damaging their earnings or reputation appear to be at an end.

abstract: Browns players locked arms during the national anthem with law enforcement agents and emergency workers.
snippet: Browns players locked arms during the national anthem with law enforcement agents and emergency workers.
lead_paragraph: Members of the Cleveland Browns and law enforcement agents and emergency workers ran onto the field together and locked arms during the national anthem on Sunday before the team’s first game of the season, defusing tension over earlier protests by some Browns players during the song.

abstract: The author of “Great House,” “The History of Love” and, most recently, “Forest Dark” prefers to read classic novels on the plane: “Twelve hours in economy is not the moment to gamble on a book.”

abstract: A two-time Pro Bowl defensive end reported on Twitter that he was held at gunpoint and handcuffed after the Mayweather-McGregor fight in Las Vegas.
snippet: A two-time Pro Bowl defensive end reported on Twitter that he was held at gunpoint and handcuffed after the Mayweather-McGregor fight in Las Vegas.
lead_paragraph: The Seattle Seahawks star Michael Bennett said he was held at gunpoint and handcuffed by the police in Las Vegas after the Mayweather-McGregor fight.

abstract: As some major designers decide not to show in New York, aesthetics face off against Instagram.
snippet: As some major designers decide not to show in New York, aesthetics face off against Instagram.
lead_paragraph: Is New York Fashion Week, which officially begins Thursday but actually begins Wednesday (thank you, Tom Ford), a dead duck? Is it a sinking ship, in the soup, up the creek? Is it — gasp! — over?
